[5]
Date: 8 Jul 2005
From: A-lan Banks <A-Lan.Banks@thomson.com>
Source: Xinhua Net
<http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2005-07/08/content_3192696.htm>


Vietnam reports 10 000 dengue fever cases
---------------------
At least 10 000 people in Vietnam's southern Mekong Delta have been
infected with dengue fever so far this year, of whom 13 died.

From 6 Jun to 7 Jul [2005], the country detected some 3 300 dengue fever
patients, including 10 fatalities, according to local newspaper Saigon
Liberation on Friday [8 Jul 2005].

Most of local sufferers are from southern localities such as the provinces
of Soc Trang, Dong Thap, Hau Giang and Bac Lieu, whose weather is most
favorable for the development of mosquitoes -the disease's transmitter.

To minimize the number of new infections, local health workers are
encouraging residents to kill mosquitoes and their larvae moreactively.
More chemicals used to kill the insect are given to the residents.

Vietnam reported 73 300 cases of dengue fever infections, including 101
fatalities last year, up 108 percent and 74 percent against the year
earlier, respectively.

